to kill for me...

48:22.778 --> 48:24.780
to get them to remember.

48:24.780 --> 48:29.785
But now he just won't stop,
that hockey puck!

48:37.251 --> 48:40.587
This isn't...real.

48:42.881 --> 48:46.343
Somebody, please, wake me up!

48:46.426 --> 48:47.636
Please!

48:58.063 --> 49:00.732
Mark! Mark, wake up!

49:00.858 --> 49:03.443
I need you to send
a little message for me.

49:03.527 --> 49:06.738
That's all,
just a little message.

49:06.738 --> 49:08.615
I'm not gonna do it.

49:08.615 --> 49:10.200
I won't do it!

49:10.200 --> 49:12.661
No?!

49:12.661 --> 49:15.455
I won't do it.

49:23.505 --> 49:29.094
I'll have to pass that message
myself, won't l?

49:34.057 --> 49:35.851
Oh, my God!

49:39.188 --> 49:42.983
Let go of me!

49:42.983 --> 49:44.568
Help...me.

49:44.568 --> 49:46.153
Mark!

49:56.163 --> 50:00.292
<i>Pass on a little
message for me, will ya?</i>

50:11.303 --> 50:14.097
Sheriff,
I've been compiling info...

50:14.181 --> 50:16.058
based on eyewitness reports
of the hockey mask killer.

50:16.058 --> 50:17.684
We already know who did this.

50:17.809 --> 50:19.686
Sheriff, we closed
down the school...

50:19.686 --> 50:21.396
and set up a curfew
for anyone under eighteen.

50:21.396 --> 50:22.523
Good.

50:22.523 --> 50:24.233
Now I want twenty-four-hour
roadblocks set up.

50:24.233 --> 50:25.818
Nobody leaves town,
nobody gets in.

50:25.859 --> 50:27.319
We're gonna contain
this son of a bitch...

50:27.319 --> 50:28.403
before he spreads any further.

50:28.487 --> 50:30.656
Yes, sir.

50:30.656 --> 50:32.491
Sir, shouldn't we have
the F.B.I. come in and--

50:32.491 --> 50:34.535
No outsiders, Stubbs.

50:34.660 --> 50:37.037
We can handle this.
We've stopped him before.

50:37.037 --> 50:39.206
OK, I'm a little lost here.

50:39.206 --> 50:40.541
Stopped who before?

50:40.541 --> 50:43.710
We don't say his name out loud.

50:43.710 --> 50:45.504
You're not from around here.

50:45.587 --> 50:46.505
I don't expect you
to understand.

50:46.547 --> 50:48.549
With all due resect, Sheriff...

50:48.549 --> 50:51.051
I think we have a copycat
of the old Jason Voorhees...

50:51.093 --> 50:52.386
Crystal Lake killer
on our hands--

50:52.386 --> 50:53.637
You listen to me.

50:53.637 --> 50:56.014
We do things around here
a certain way for a reason...

50:56.056 --> 50:58.308
and that's given us
four years of peace.

50:58.392 --> 51:00.394
So you either do your job
and keep your mouth shut...

51:00.394 --> 51:02.437
or, so help me God,
I will lock you up!

51:02.563 --> 51:04.815
Do you understand me?!

51:07.776 --> 51:08.819
Yes, sir.

51:19.121 --> 51:20.873
Why don't we all just leave?

51:20.873 --> 51:25.419
No, even if we leave,
Freddy can still get us.

51:25.502 --> 51:28.755
We all know about him.
We're all afraid of him.

51:30.465 --> 51:34.928
It was our fear that
gave him his power.

51:35.012 --> 51:37.472
We're marked now.

51:37.556 --> 51:39.266
Man, screw that clown.

51:39.308 --> 51:40.642
I mean, what kind
of a pussy...

51:40.767 --> 51:42.269
comes after you
in your dreams anyway?

51:42.352 --> 51:45.189
Now, that big-ass mother fucker
back at the cornfield...

51:45.314 --> 51:47.399
all right, that's who
we should be afraid of.

51:47.399 --> 51:49.568
Tell me who
the fuck that was.

51:49.610 --> 51:51.862
His name was Jason Voorhees.

51:51.862 --> 51:55.073
Shit, man...um...

51:55.073 --> 51:57.868
How'd you know
we were here?

51:57.951 --> 51:59.995
Nothing personal,
but the Scooby van out back...

52:00.120 --> 52:01.747
wasn't exactly subtle.

52:01.747 --> 52:03.999
And never keep
your keys in the door.

52:04.124 --> 52:06.251
Great, so now we're
completely fucked.

52:06.251 --> 52:08.128
No, you're not.

52:08.170 --> 52:10.547
I'm here to help you.

52:10.672 --> 52:13.258
Now, this Jason Voorhees
supposedly drowned...

52:13.258 --> 52:15.677
at Camp Crystal Lake
back in 1957...

52:15.761 --> 52:17.471
when he was
eleven years old.

52:17.471 --> 52:20.182
The counselors weren't
watching him...

52:20.182 --> 52:22.851
then they made the mistake
of killing his mother.

52:22.851 --> 52:24.978
The legend has it...

52:24.978 --> 52:27.356
that Jason kept returning
from his grave...

52:27.356 --> 52:29.233
to punish whoever
returned to the camp.

52:29.233 --> 52:32.027
I think we're dealing
with a copycat here.

52:32.027 --> 52:33.529
No. No. No, no, no.

52:33.570 --> 52:35.030
He's not a copycat.

52:35.030 --> 52:36.615
I've seen what he can do.
He's the real Jason.

52:36.615 --> 52:38.867
That's impossible, Linderman.
Jason is dead.

52:38.867 --> 52:41.912
You'd better start thinking
outside your little box, dude...

52:41.954 --> 52:43.497
'cause somebody's
definitely breaking...

52:43.580 --> 52:45.499
the fucking reality rules, OK?

52:45.582 --> 52:46.875
It makes sense in a way.

52:46.875 --> 52:50.295
I mean, what if Freddy
brought Jason back...

52:50.379 --> 52:52.506
because he was too weak
to go after us on his own...

52:52.506 --> 52:55.008
so he used Jason.

52:55.008 --> 52:57.010
I mean, he knew that
we'd think it was him...

52:57.052 --> 52:58.512
that we'd spread
the fear again.

52:58.512 --> 52:59.680
And now that it's working...

52:59.721 --> 53:02.224
